  "prompt": "How is Matt LeBlanc (Joey Tribbiani of Friends) in real life?",
  "response": "Matt LeBlanc, best known for his role as Joey Tribbiani on the iconic sitcom \"Friends,\" is quite different from his character in real life. Outside of his acting career, LeBlanc is known for being down-to-earth and approachable. He has a more reserved personality compared to the outgoing and often comedic nature of Joey.\n\nLeBlanc has a passion for cars and motorsports; he hosted the BBC show's \"Top Gear\" from 2016 to 2019, showcasing his love for driving and automotive culture. He has also been involved in other successful television projects, including the spin-off \"Joey\" and the CBS sitcom \"Man with a Plan.\"\n\nIn terms of personal life, LeBlanc is known to keep his private life relatively low-key. He has a daughter named Marina, and he places great importance on family. Overall, while he is a successful actor, he tends to lead a more private life than the flashy persona of his most famous character.",
